###

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

# NOTE: Run Projects.http first to create a project and get a valid projectId.
# Replace {{projectId}} and {{memberToken}} with actual values from your test run.

# ── Snapshot ────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get snapshot as project member
# Requires: a valid projectId and a token from a project member
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/ProjectSnapshot HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{memberToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: smoke-test-snapshot-001

# Expected: 200 OK with JSON body containing TemplateContent

### Get snapshot as non-member (should be 403 Forbidden)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/ProjectSnapshot HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{nonMemberToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: smoke-test-snapshot-002

# Expected: 403 Forbidden

### Get snapshot for non-existent project (should be 403 Forbidden)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/projects/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/ProjectSnapshot HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{memberToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: smoke-test-snapshot-003

# Expected: 403 Forbidden

### Get snapshot without token (should be 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/projects/{{projectId}}/ProjectSnapshot HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: smoke-test-snapshot-004

# Expected: 401 Unauthorized
